‘Somewhere to sit and think of you
Peter Graves 1951 - 2012
Joyful days in this park collecting children from school -
a truly wonderful father
Missed by your wife and children
more than we can put into words"ř
ŘEvan George King
Beloved father and "Grandpa Ducks"
Who not only fished his son out of Queen's Park Pond once
but twice in one day!
Remembered with love.

Muriel King
Beloved mother and "Nana Ducks"
Loved to bring her children and grandchildren to this park
and spending time with her family.
Missed and loved.

In loving memory of Auntie Edna,
who loved coming to this park
and always had a joke to share.
Fondly remembered by Brian & Ronnie King
and family."„
